#1 Rectal cancer, adenocarcinoma
Mr. Bailey has had a recent diagnosis of invasive moderately differentiated adenocarcinoma which was confirmed here as grade 3/4 by our pathologist.  He will need to undergo additional staging workup in addition to his CT of the abdomen and pelvis that he has had.  Of note, he had a CEA done on June 16, 2010, which was 1.1.  These records will be scanned in.  Subsequent staging will include MRI of the pelvis, EUS with the request to tattoo a region 1-cm distal to the lesion for future reference as well as basic laboratory workup.  He will also have a surgical evaluation in followup with Ms. Barron before that time.  We will also try to obtain the actual colonoscopy report from the outside hospital.  The above was discussed with Dr. Flores and Ms. Barron, and they agree with what is stated above.
Supervising physician, Dr. Flores.
ADVANCE DIRECTIVES
Advance directive or living will: No, not interested in additional information.

